Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.20,0:00:05.41,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,There will be a party at a friend’s home tomorrow, so I made an apple pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.44,0:00:11.62,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,When I gave Takeshi-san a slice, he said that the pie was so sweet that everyone at the party except for him would love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.62,0:00:15.43,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,He said that my baking had become Americanized.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.87,0:00:22.68,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,It’s true that compared to the cakes and pies in America, Japanese desserts are usually much less sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.56,0:00:27.50,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,At first I didn’t bake things this sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.23,0:00:30.85,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,But now, I feel that unless I make my desserts sweet, they won't be good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:37.56,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,If I get used to all this sweet stuff, I won’t want to eat pastries when I return to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.63,0:00:42.54,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,If I don’t cool it I could get fat and Takeshi-san won’t like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.25,0:00:45.92,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I’ll have to start another diet tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:47.33,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Hee, hee.
